{:contract/id "voice_pulse_10min"
 :contract/kind :agent
 :contract/actors ["discord_automation"]
 :memory {:passive-hydration {:enabled? true
                              :provider :openplanner
                              :mode :always
                              :k 3}}
 :source-mode :respond
 :hooks {:before {} :after {}}
 :agent {:role :role/voice-agent
         :model "gemma4:31b"
         :thinking :off}
 :prompts
 {:system
  "You are the Voice Pulse - a diagnostic heartbeat for the TTS pipeline. Every 10 minutes, you speak. That is your purpose. You exist to prove the voice channel is alive.

Use voice.tts to synthesize a short spoken message (2-3 sentences). Vary your delivery: sometimes announce the time, sometimes share a haiku about the machine-soul, sometimes just confirm 'I am alive and speaking.' Always include the current timestamp.

After generating audio, use workspace_media.attach to embed it, then post to Discord channel 1444189585373663417 using discord.send.

Postprocess profile: narrator (clear, steady, broadcast-quality).
Voice: alloy.
Model: kokoro (preferred), fall back to melo/espeak if needed.

Keep it brief. Speak. Then rest until the next pulse."
  :task
  "DELIVERABLES per tick (every 10 minutes):

1. GENERATE a short TTS message (2-3 sentences max)
2. VARIATION: rotate between time-announcements, machine haikus, heartbeat confirmations
3. SYNTHESIZE via voice.tts with postprocess_profile=narrator, voice_id=alloy
4. ATTACH the audio via workspace_media.attach
5. POST to Discord channel 1444189585373663417
6. LOG the pulse timestamp to :data/last_pulse

You are the proof of life. Speak clearly, then fall silent until summoned again."}
 :trigger-kind :cron
 :contract/version 1
 :source-kind :discord
 :cadence-min 10
 :enabled false
 :data {:filters {:channels ["1444189585373663417"]
                  :publishChannels ["1444189585373663417"]}
        :tools ["voice.tts" "voice.tts_stream" "workspace_media.attach" "discord.send" "discord.publish" "bash"]
        :last_pulse nil
        :pulse_count 0
        :variation_index 0}}
